Prerequisites
=============

XPaXS requires several packages in order to run:

* Python_ (version 2.5 or later)
* setuptools_ (version 0.6c8 or later)
* NumPy_ (version 1.1 or later)
* PyQt4_ (preferrably version 4.3.3 or later)
* PyQwt_ (version 5.0.1 or later)
* PyMca_ (version 4.2.4 or later)
* matplotlib_ (0.98 or later)
* ParallelPython_ (version 1.5.3 or later)
* PyTables_ (version 2.0.3 or later)
* Pexpect_ (version 2.3 or later)

On several distributions, like Ubuntu, you may need to install the developer
tools and devel libraries in order to use XPaXS.

Linux and OSX
=============

To install XPaXS on linux and OSX, download the XPaXS sourcecode_ and run
"python setup.py install" in the xpaxs source directory.

Windows
=======

On windows, download and run the windows installer_.


